text: People sigh about "simpler times" but we were kids then and we didn't understand how complicated things really were. I though my childhood was a simple but there was Vietnam and all the social unrest going on that I just didn't know about. To me, Watergate was just some annoying thing that pre-empted all the good TV shows. But it's true, we tend to look back with rose-colored glasses and not remember the bad stuff. You didn't hear about divorce because divorced people were shunned. There single mothers everywhere because husbands were killed in various wars. If you were born out of wedlock, you were viewed as unclean somehow, even though you had done nothing wrong. Not to mention the sexism, racism, homophobia, and other dark sides to life in the past....like all the unemployment that came with the Great Depression, or the interning of innocent Japanese-Americans during WWII. The music is nice but let's not get too mired in the nostalgia trap. This modern age has its drawbacks but I have several health problems and am VERY thankful to be living in the 21st century!
